  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.1All Creatio products\nOn this page\nTo add an article:\n1. **Open** the **Knowledge base** section.\n2. **Click New**. This opens a page.\n3. **Fill** out the article fields.\n**Field**| **Field value**  \n---|---  \nTitle| Enter the name of the knowledge base article.  \nType| Select the type of the knowledge base article, for example, \"Rules and regulations\" or \"FAQ.\"  \nRich text| Add the article itself. The field supports rich text.  \n4. Open the Attachments tab and **add relevant files** , for example, documents related to the knowledge base article. To do this, drag the relevant file or click the ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/Composable_apps/Knowledge_Management/create_a_knowledge_base_article/btn_upload.png) button and select the file in the upload window.\n5. Click ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/Composable_apps/Knowledge_Management/create_a_knowledge_base_article/btn_access_permissions.png) to **set up access permissions for the article** (optional). Learn more: [Share records](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1014).\n6. **Save the changes**.\n**As a result** , Creatio will add an article to the knowledge base list.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Knowledge Management overview](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2472)\n[Integrate with landing pages and web forms](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1081)\n[Set up a product catalog](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1226)",
